{"HERS":[{"def":"See the Note under Her, pr.","pos":""}],"HERSCHELIAN":[{"def":"Of or relating to Sir William Herschel; as, the Herschelian telescope.","pos":""}],"HERSE":[{"def":"A kind of gate or portcullis, having iron bars, like a harrow, studded with iron spikes.","pos":""}],"HERSELF":[{"def":"An emphasized form of the third person feminine pronoun; -- used as a subject with she; as, she herself will bear the blame; also used alone in the predicate, either in the nominative or objective case; as, it is herself; she blames herself.","pos":""},{"def":"Her own proper, true, or real character; hence, her right, or sane, mind; as, the woman was deranged, but she is now herself again; she has come to herself.","pos":""}],"HERSILLON":[{"def":"A beam with projecting spikes, used to make a breach impassable.","pos":""}]}